array[file] — multiple attachments (closes gap Б3)

A new TyArrayFile kind wired through the whole pipeline: the type parser
(array[file]), value validation (an array of {hash,...} file refs, each hash
required), UI metadata (array_file), MCP describe_entity, structured authoring
(compose_pack / FieldTypes), and the grammar.

Incident now has `attachments: array[file]` (screenshots + logs). The dogfood
proves it: an incident round-trips two attachments, and a malformed one (no
hash) is rejected with a validation error.

This was the last of blockers Б1–Б7 from APPS-GAP-PLAN — the functional cores of
the HR / CRM / Service Desk apps now build on the kernel without kernel gaps.
